SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS A NONPROFIT CORPORATION UNDER THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE ("CODE") SECTION 501(C)(6). BASED ON THIS CLASSIFICATION, THE ORGANIZATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES AS WELL AS SALES AND USE TAX UNDER THE LAWS OF THE STATE OF FLORIDA. DURING THE YEARS ENDED SEPTEMBER 30, 2018 AND 2017, THE ORGANIZATION GENERATED NET UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME FROM CERTAIN ALTERNATIVE ACTIVITIES. NO PROVISIONS FOR FEDERAL OR STATE TAXES WERE RECORDED AS THE AMOUNTS WERE IMMATERIAL TO THESE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZES AND MEASURES TAX POSITIONS BASED ON THEIR TECHNICAL MERIT AND ASSESSES THE LIKELIHOOD THAT THE POSITIONS WILL BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BASED ON THE FACTS, CIRCUMSTANCES AND INFORMATION AVAILABLE AT THE END OF EACH PERIOD. INTEREST AND PENALTIES ON TAX LIABILITIES, IF ANY, WOULD BE RECORDED IN INTEREST EXPENSE AND OTHER NON-INTEREST EXPENSE, RESPECTIVELY. THE U.S. FEDERAL JURISDICTION IS THE MAJOR TAX JURISDICTION WHERE THE ORGANIZATION FILES INCOME TAX RETURNS. THE ORGANIZATION IS GENERALLY NO LONGER SUBJECT TO U.S. FEDERAL EXAMINATIONS BY TAX AUTHORITIES FOR YEARS BEFORE 2015.
